    • specialOpCheck

      Double specialOpCheck()
      Will check which number (current input or running total) to use the special op on (square or sqrt). If running total, will set the running total to zero. If currnt input is an error, will show an error sign.
      Returns:
      the number to do the special op on or null if error

    • square

      void square()
      Will square the current number on screen: either running total or current input then set the current input as the square number

    • sqrt

      void sqrt()
      Will sqrt the current number on screen: either running total or current input then set the current input as the sqrt number. if the current number is invalid input: '<' 0, will produce an error message
